    "body": "### Contact Details (e.g. Tox ID or email)\n\nfloppy\n\n### Feature Description\n\nThe safest way to get the IP address of a domain is to use a DoH/DoT resolver, but the DoH/DoT resolver's IP address also needs to be determined.\nWe need the ability to specify DoH/DoT resolver and to check that its own IP address is correct somehow.\nAs an option we can resolve it using the system's DNS resolver, and show it's IP address, so that the user can check it.\nOr we need to specify it's IP address independently if for some reasons the user can not trust system's DNS resolver.\nAfter that, http/socks with domain names should be available for use. Those domain names will be resolved with DoH/DoT only.\n\n### Contribution\n\n- [ ] I would like to contribute to this feature",
